import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['index'] = pd.to_datetime(data['index'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['u'] = pd.to_numeric(data['u'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
